mae present in the female. Small and delicate skull. Large tympanic bullae. First upper incisors are pointed forward. Elevated crown of lower second premolar biscuspid. This is a common resident in Kuwait (Clayton, 1983; Clayton & Wells, 1987; Harrison & Bates, 1991; Al-Sirhan, 2021; Pope, 2012). Specimens from Kuwait are found in the BMNH and HZM collections. Additional records are in Khalil & Abdul Salam (1985). An inhabitant of Al-Jalia desert area southeast Kuwait (Eissa et al., 1975). One specimen of Hemiechinus auratus from Salimieh is found at the FMNH. One specimen of Hemiechinus auratus from Ali Al Salem Air Force Base is found at the SMNH. It feeds on various insects, centipedes and land", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "86819141-7e18-40e4-8af9-360d4f822c1a": {"__data__": {"id_": "86819141-7e18-40e4-8af9-360d4f822c1a", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/mammals-state-kuwait", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Mammals of the State of Kuwait", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/mammals-state-kuwait", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "e9915db96344fa0c181d57d4b5e23b54850dc93bb9985648ed0eebf4effb2e02"}, "3": {"node_id": "b8e28705-5f6d-4c10-9fa7-c39d2fe09a45", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/mammals-state-kuwait", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conserv